post_text:
Good afternoon Panther Nation!

We hope this message finds you and your family doing well. We know everyone is anticipating the beginning of the 2020-2021 school year. If you have not already done so, please log in to Family Access to complete online registration for the 2020-2021 school year.

We have received many questions regarding our learning options for the upcoming school year. You, as a parent will choose whether your student will learn face-to-face on campus, or at home virtually. Below you will find an informational letter explaining the 2 learning options. During the registration process you will be able to choose which learning option will work best for your child.

We are looking forward to the start of the new school year!:

https://www.mabankisd.net/upload/page/0060/2021_Learning_Options_Information_Letter.pdf

post_text:
We would like to thank our students, families, and faculty for another successful Fill the Bus Food Drive! What a wonderful way to start this Thanksgiving break! The Mabank Area Good Samaritans and Care and Share food banks received the items donated which will benefit families in our community. Proud to be a Panther!

Edit: We would also like to give a big thank you to the MISD maintenance department for helping to pack and transport the donations. They are truly our behind the scenes heroes!

Three big events this week. The students would like (and deserve) crowd support....

First... Wednesday the Mabank HS Band is in Mesquite for UIL Marching Contest. They take the field at about 4PM. Go support our band please.

Second... Friday the Mabank HS Varsity Volleyball team is in Van at 4:30 PM. The girls are competing for a good playoff spot. Go support our girls please.

Third... Friday the Mabank HS Varsity Football team is at Waxahachie Life at 7:30 PM. The boys are currently tied with Life School. It should be a great game.

Our students are representing our community at a high level. They appreciate those who go out and support them.

2:00 1/2 and 3/4 grade BOYS

This committee is made up of community members, staff members and students.

I hope all of you will join me.

On Friday evening, prior to the Panther Homecoming Football game, the Mabank Athletic Booster club will be selling Street Taco Dinners, complete with rice, beans, and trimmings, for $10 per meal (while supplies last). Meals will be available at South end of Panther Stadium with 100% of all proceeds benefiting the Mercer Family.

Checks for this event may be made payable to the Mabank Athletic Booster Club OR The Mercer Family Tragedy Account. Please join us in supporting these Mabank ISD students in their time of need!

post_text:
Friends,

We encourage the use of Social Media in our organization as a resource for one-way communication of events and celebrations.

We enjoy sharing the success of our school district.

We discourage the use of social media for resolving problems or presenting one side of a negative situation.

Professionals deserve a chance to resolve concerns with appropriate face-to-face discussion.

Concerns with MISD staff, procedures or policies should be taken straight to the person who can most efficiently resolve the concern.

You may find the contacts for those people at www.mabankisd.net.

This is how we will grow together.
